.info-block
  %p.lead
    Shelr.tv allows You to record
    something interesting from your terminal and
    share it to your followers.
  %p.lead
    It almost the same thing as YouTube but for plain
    text shellcasts. You can copy and paste everything You see.
  
  %h2 Quickstart on Linux

  %p Install ruby and rubygems for your distribution
  %pre
    %code
      = preserve do
        :escaped
          gem install shelr
          shelr record

  %h2 Quickstart on OSX

  %p Install ruby and rubygems
  
  %p
    Install ttyrec via
    %a{ :href => 'http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/' } homebrew
    
  %pre
    %code
      = preserve do
        :escaped
          brew install ttyrec

  %pre
    %code
      = preserve do
        :escaped
          gem install shelr
          shelr record
    
    
